{"word":"H1845 - דְּעוּאֵל - Dᵉʻûwʼêl - deh-oo-ale' - Deuel","slug":"H1845","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דְּעוּאֵל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Dᵉʻûwʼêl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>deh-oo-ale'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Deuel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>דּעוּאל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>de‛û'êl</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>deh-oo-ale'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Deuel = \"they know God\" <ol><li>father of Eliasaph, the captain of the tribe of Gad at the time of the numbering of the people at Sinai, also called 'Reuel'</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H3045\">H3045</a> and <a href=\"#/H410\">H410</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1843\">H1843</a>, <a href=\"#/H1844\">H1844</a>, <a href=\"#/H1847\">H1847</a>, <a href=\"#/H3037\">H3037</a>, <a href=\"#/H3043\">H3043</a>, <a href=\"#/H3045\">H3045</a>, <a href=\"#/H3047\">H3047</a>, <a href=\"#/H3048\">H3048</a>, <a href=\"#/H3049\">H3049</a>, <a href=\"#/H4069\">H4069</a>, <a href=\"#/H4093\">H4093</a>, <a href=\"#/H4129\">H4129</a>, <a href=\"#/H4130\">H4130</a>"}]}